verbose_text: This study showed that the higher the severity of CHD, the higher the level of FIB in the body and the higher the level of inflammation in the body, which may be related to the fact that FIB can stimulate the proliferation and migration of vascular smooth muscle cells, increase the blood viscosity, slow down the blood flow, accelerate the process of arteriosclerosis, and lead to severe arterial stenosis.
